<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>VocabVault</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/grammarPage.css" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Great+Vibes&family=Knewave&family=Margarine&family=Mogra&family=Roboto+Flex:opsz,wght@8..144,100..1000&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Quick grammar review</h1>
    <p class="descr">Let's have a look what you've learnt!</p>
    <hr />

    <p>Beginner (A1 - A2)</p>
    <section id="A1-A2">
      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Nouns & Articles</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Gender: Nouns are masculine or feminine. Masculine often uses le
            (e.g., le chien), feminine uses la (e.g., la maison).
          </li>
          <li>
            Plural: Add -s to nouns for plural, use les for plural articles (les
            chiens).
          </li>
          <li>Indefinite Articles: un (m), une (f), des (pl).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Adjectives</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Agreement: Match gender and number of the noun (un livre vert, une
            maison verte).
          </li>
          <li>
            Placement: Generally follow the noun (une voiture rouge), but some
            come before (un beau jour).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Pronouns</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Subject: je, tu, il/elle, nous, vous, ils/elles.</li>
          <li>Object: me, te, le/la, nous, vous, les.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Present Tense of Verbs</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Object: me, te, le/la, nous, vous, les.
            <ol>
              <li>-er: parler → je parle, tu parles, il parle...</li>
              <li>-re: vendre → je vends, tu vends, il vend...</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
          <li>
            Irregular Verbs:Common ones include être, avoir, aller, faire.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Basic Sentence Structure</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Subject + Verb + Object: Je mange une pomme.</li>
          <li>Questions: Verb + Subject + Object: Manges-tu une pomme ?</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Numbers</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Cardinal: un, deux, trois...</li>
          <li>Ordinal: premier, deuxième, troisième...</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Time and Date</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Time: Il est trois heures.</li>
          <li>Date: Nous sommes le 3 janvier.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
    <hr />

    <p>Intermediate (B1 - B2)</p>
    <section id="B1-B2">
      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Past Tenses</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Passé Composé (completed actions): J’ai parlé, tu as fini, il a
            vendu.
          </li>
          <li>
            Plus-Que-Parfait: J’avais parlé, tu avais fini, il avait vendu.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Future and Conditional</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Future Simple: Add endings to infinitive: je parlerai, tu finiras,
            il vendra.
          </li>
          <li>
            Conditional: Add endings to infinitive: je parlerais, tu finirais,
            il vendrait.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Subjunctive Mood</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Present Subjunctive: Express wishes, doubts, or emotions. Formed by
            switching endings:
            <ol>
              <li>que je parle, que tu parles, qu’il parle...</li>
              <li>Triggered by expressions like il faut que, je veux que.</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Pronouns with Commands</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Positive: Attach to verb (Donne-le-moi).</li>
          <li>Negative: Before verb (Ne me le donne pas).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Prepositions</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Common Uses: à (to), de (of/from), avec (with).</li>
          <li>Expressions: avoir besoin de, aller à Paris.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <p>Advanced (C1 - C2)</p>
    <section id="C1-C2">
      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Complex Subjunctive Uses</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Past Subjunctive: Used for hypothetical or past doubts/wishes. que
            j’aie parlé, que tu aies fini.
          </li>
          <li>
            If Clauses:
            <ol>
              <li>Possible: Si je travaille, je réussis.</li>
              <li>Hypothetical: Si je travaillais, je réussirais.</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Passive Voice</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Formed with être + past participle: Le livre a été lu.</li>
          <li>Reflexive verbs used for general statements: Ça se dit.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Perfect Tenses</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Present Perfect: J’ai parlé, tu as fini.</li>
          <li>Past Perfect: J’avais parlé, tu avais fini.</li>
          <li>Future Perfect: J’aurai parlé, tu auras fini.</li>
          <li>Conditional Perfect: J’aurais parlé, tu aurais fini.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Advanced Sentence Structure</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Relative Pronouns: qui, que, dont, lequel.</li>
          <li>Indirect Speech: Il a dit qu’il viendrait.</li>
          <li>
            Complex Constructions: Use of gerunds (en mangeant) and infinitives
            (après avoir parlé).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <script>
      const dropdownBtns = document.querySelectorAll(".dropdownBtn");
      const dropdownLists = document.querySelectorAll(".dropdownList");

      dropdownBtns.forEach((btn, index) => {
        btn.addEventListener("click", function () {
          const dropdownList = dropdownLists[index];
          dropdownList.style.display =
            dropdownList.style.display === "block" ? "none" : "block";
        });
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
